---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Relocation Cost Estimator | How Much Does It Cost to Move Abroad?"
description: "Estimate the total cost of relocating internationally. Calculate visa fees, flights, housing deposits, health insurance, and more for your move abroad."
---

{% block structuredData %}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "WebApplication",
      "name": "Relocation Cost Estimator",
      "url": "{{ site.url }}/tools/relocation-calculator/",
      "description": "{{ description }}",
      "applicationCategory": "FinanceApplication",
      "operatingSystem": "Any",
      "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "EUR" },
      "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "{{ site.name }}", "url": "{{ site.url }}" }
    },
    {
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much does it cost to relocate abroad for a tech job?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "The total cost of relocating abroad for a tech job typically ranges from €5,000 to €25,000 depending on the destination city, family size, and shipping needs. Major cost factors include flights (€400-€1,200), first month rent plus deposit (2-3 months rent), visa fees (€100-€2,500), health insurance, and initial living expenses."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What should my employer cover in a relocation package?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "A good employer relocation package typically covers visa sponsorship fees, flights for you and your family, temporary housing (1-3 months), moving or shipping allowance, and sometimes a lump-sum relocation bonus. Top companies like Zalando, Booking.com, and Spotify offer comprehensive packages."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How can I reduce the cost of relocating abroad?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "You can reduce relocation costs by negotiating a better relocation package, shipping only essentials, staying in temporary furnished housing before committing to a lease, using shared housing initially, and taking advantage of tax benefits like the Netherlands 30% ruling or Germany's relocation expense deductions."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much emergency fund should I have when relocating?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Financial advisors recommend having at least 2-3 months of living expenses saved as an emergency fund when relocating abroad. This covers unexpected costs, delays in first salary payment, and provides a safety net while you settle into your new city."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
</script>
{% endblock %}

